com.b2international.snowowl.snomed.core.domain.refset

Class SnomedReferenceSetMember

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.b2international.snowowl.core.domain.BaseComponent
      • com.b2international.snowowl.snomed.core.domain.SnomedComponent
        • com.b2international.snowowl.snomed.core.domain.refset.SnomedReferenceSetMember
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IComponent, java.io.Serializable

    public final class SnomedReferenceSetMember
extends SnomedComponent
    Represents a SNOMED CT Reference Set Member.
    Reference sets returned by search requests are populated based on the expand parameters passed into the BaseResourceRequestBuilder#setExpand(String) methods. The expand parameters can be nested allowing a fine control for the details returned in the resultset. The supported expand parameters are:

    • targetComponent() - returns the target component of the member
    • referencedComponent() - returns the referenced component of the member
    Expand parameters can be nested to further expand or filter the details returned. For example:

    referencedComponent(expand(pt())), would return the preferred term of a Concept type referenced component.

    Since:
    4.5
    See Also:
    SnomedConcept, SnomedDescription, SnomedRelationship, SnomedReferenceSet, Serialized Form
